headline: Discount retailer stocks in focus on Trump's proposed tariffs
summary: Discount retailer stocks like Dollar General (DG), Dollar Tree (DLTR), and Five Below (FIVE), and footwear companies Skechers (SKX) are in focus after former President Donald Trump won reelection. Yahoo Finance's Brooke DiPalma examines the stock moves as investors assess the impact of Trump's second term, primarily his proposed tariff plans, and looks at e.l.f. Beauty (ELF) stock after the Dollar General partner reported earnings. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.

headline: Dollar Tree, Five Below downgraded at KeyBanc on China import exposure
summary: Investing.com -- KeyBanc Capital Markets analysts revised their ratings for Dollar Tree (NASDAQ:DLTR) and Five Below (NASDAQ:FIVE) stocks, downgrading both to Sector Weight from Overweight.
